. maj 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31. maj 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"omkring 1451","4 June 1503":"4. juni 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England"},"nl":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"circa 1451–31 mei 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31 mei 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"circa 1451","4 June 1503":"4 juni 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England"},"en":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"about 1451–31 May 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31 May 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"about 1451","4 June 1503":"4 June 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hilton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire):","habitational name from any of various places called Hilton (e.g. in Cambridgeshire, Derbyshire, Staffordshire, North Yorkshire, and Westmorland), most of which derive from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though some come from Old English <i>helde</i> ‘slope’ + <i>tūn</i>.","occasionally, as in the case of Ralph <i>filius Hilton</i> (Yorkshire 1219), perhaps from the personal name <i>Hilton</i>, itself a possible form of Norman <i>Hildun</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’ + <i>hūn</i> ‘bear cub’. Compare   Hilt  . This English surname is present in Ireland (mainly taken to Ulster in the early 17th century, though recorded earlier in Dublin)."],"variants":[{"name":"Hylton","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Hilton  ."]},{"name":"Hulton","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Hulton (Lancashire) or Hulton (Staffordshire), both from Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Hilton  ."]},{"name":"Hilt","meanings":["German: from a short form of   Hildebrand   or some other compound ancient Germanic name formed with <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’ as the first element. See   Hild  .","English (London): from the Middle English personal name <i>Hilte</i>, ultimately from ancient Germanic <i>Helto</i>, probably from <i>halith-</i> ‘hero’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":4,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William Hilton was born about 1451, in Durham, England. He married Margery Bowes. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He was buried in Hilton, Durham, England."},"et":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"umbes 1451–31. mai 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31. mai 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"umbes 1451","4 June 1503":"4. juuni 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England"},"fi":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"noin 1451–31. toukokuuta 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31. toukokuuta 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"noin 1451","4 June 1503":"4. kesäkuuta 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England"},"fr":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"environ 1451–31 mai 1506","1443–1503":"1443–1503","1488–1537":"1488–1537","1451–1506":"1451–1506","31 May 1506":"31 mai 1506","1503":"1503","1488":"1488","1455":"1455","1443":"1443","1451":"1451","about 1451":"environ 1451","4 June 1503":"4 juin 1503","1506":"1506","1537":"1537","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hilton, Durham, England":"Hilton, Durham, Angleterre","Durham, England":"Durham, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Hilton est né environ 1451, à Durham, Angleterre. Il a épousé Margery Bowes. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Ilenterré à Hilton, Durham, Angleterre."},"de":{"about 1451–31 May 1506":"um 1451–31